        "sender_full_name": "Bhavik Mehta",
        "timestamp": 1730998180
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Actually, how feasible is it for <code>extBinders</code> to support multiple identifiers? Then we'd get the best of both worlds here.</p>",
        "id": 481473534,
        "sender_full_name": "Bhavik Mehta",
        "timestamp": 1731169101
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And make the default exists/for all use extBinders?</p>",
        "id": 481473694,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1731169256
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We're looking into improving the binder situation. It'd be nice if binders across all quantifiers could be more consistent!</p>\n<p>I remember for BigOperators I made a variant of extBinders that had nicer properties, but I'd need to remind myself what they solved and why they didn't support <code>x y z : T</code> either. <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/42ff2ccb6d99b39a65e43b8da21a60f8e7d3f9ca/Mathlib/Algebra/BigOperators/Group/Finset.lean#L93-L104\">https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/42ff2ccb6d99b39a65e43b8da21a60f8e7d3f9ca/Mathlib/Algebra/BigOperators/Group/Finset.lean#L93-L104</a></p>",
